# Git Workflow

## Branches

- Create a feature branch for each feature or fix.
- Never commit directly to `main` unless explicitly instructed.

## Commits

- Use Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`, `chore:`).
- Write descriptive commit messages focused on why, not just what.
- Never commit failing code — run validation (`testing.mdc`) before committing.
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, API keys).

## Push and Pull Requests

- Push only when explicitly instructed.
- Create Pull Requests only when explicitly instructed.
- Never force-push to `main` or `master`.

## Commit safety

- Never update git config.
- Never skip hooks unless explicitly instructed.
- Never amend commits that have been pushed unless explicitly instructed.
